{
  "texts": [
    "lptC PCR products were inserted into pET22/42 with a C-terminal thrombin cleavage site and a His7 tag.",
    "Oligonucleotide primers were purchased from Eton Biosciences or Genewiz.",
    "Plasmids and strains used in this study are reported in Supplementary Tables 8 and 9 with plasmid sequences provided.",
    "Culture, genetic manipulation and MIC measurements of A. baylyi ADP1 were conducted according to previously reported procedures 56, 57.",
    "Point mutants were constructed in a two-step procedure as described previously 58 with the introduction and excision of the integration cassette at codon 66 of pepA, wherein the excising fragment of otherwise wild-type chromosomal DNA sequence from codon 406 of pepA to codon 193 of lptG bore the desired mutation, and the resulting clones were screened by amplicon sequencing from codon 81 of holC to codon 501 of gpmI."
  ]
}